To create an iOS app or Andriod apps using Python, you can use frameworks like Kivy or BeeWare's Briefcase.Kivy is an open-source Python framework for developing multi-touch applications. It is particularly well-suited for the creation of cross-platform applications, including those targeting Android and iOS devices. Kivy is designed to be easy to use and allows developers to write code once and deploy it on multiple platforms without major modifications.
